sh
# Interpreter for 'vpn-switch session remove <PID>' command
# Terminal function that generates shell commands to remove session directory
#
# Default value: "sh"
#   Executes commands to remove .session/<PID>/ directory and contents
#   Includes safety check: refuses to remove if process still alive
#
# Removal is permanent - session metadata cannot be recovered.
# Use 'session remove' to clean up stale sessions (dead processes).
#
# Safety features:
#   - Validates session exists before removal
#   - Checks if process alive (kill -0)
#   - Refuses removal if process still running
#
# Example usage:
#   vpn-switch session remove 12345  # Remove stale session
#
# Advanced - dry-run mode:
#   echo "cat" > .env/local/VPN_SWITCH_INTERPRETER_session_remove
#   vpn-switch session remove 12345  # Preview commands without executing
